Privacy Policy
MBC Now values your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data in compliance with the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia’s Personal Data Protection Law (PDPL). This notice outlines our practices related to the collection, use, storage, and sharing of your data, ensuring transparency and responsibility.
Personal Data We Collect
• Types of Data Collected:
Identifiable Information:
This includes, but is not limited to, names, contact details, and demographic information such as age, gender, and preferences.
Financial Data:
We collect financial information such as payment transaction tokens generated by payment gateways for processing transactions securely.
How We Use Your Personal Data
• Purpose-Driven Processing:
Service Delivery:
We use your data to register and manage your accounts, process your subscriptions, and ensure the delivery of services you have signed up for.
Legal Compliance and Contractual Necessities:
We process your data based on the legal ground of explicit consent and, where applicable, to fulfill our contractual obligations.
Legal Compliance and Contractual Necessities:
Retention Practices:
We retain personal data only as long as necessary for the specific purposes for which it was collected. While our retention periods vary depending on the type of data and legal requirements, we commit to not retaining personal data beyond the duration required to serve the legitimate purpose.
Retention Practices:
Third-Party Sharing:
We share your personal data with trusted third parties only when necessary for the service delivery, under stringent contractual safeguards.
International Transfers:
Personal data may be transferred across borders to locations where our data processing facilities are located. These transfers are conducted in compliance with applicable data protection laws and ensure adequate levels of protection.
Protecting Your Privacy
Security Measures:
We implement robust technical and organizational measures to protect your personal data against unauthorized access, alteration, and all other unlawful forms of processing.
Your Data Privacy Rights
Exercising Your Rights:
You have the right to access, correct, update, or request deletion of your personal data. Please contact our Data Protection Officer at dataprotection@mbc.net for any concerns or requests regarding your data.
Exercising Your Rights:
Updates and Revisions:
We may update this notice periodically to reflect changes in our data processing practices. Significant updates will be communicated to you through our official channels.
For further details or inquiries, please contact us at
dataprotection@mbc.net
We use cookies to personalize and enhance your experience on our site. Visit our
Privacy Policy
page to learn more. By using our site, you agree to our use of cookies.
